description:
The ABCpdf .NET Gecko runtime for HTML to PDF conversion using the Firefox rendering engine.

ABCpdf operates two HTML rendering engines for insertion of HTML content. The MSHTML engine leverages IE as installed on the local machine. The Gecko runtime adds Firefox-style HTML rendering to the mix.

Placed HTML support means your HTML can be treated just like any other media - placed wherever you like on the page. Paged HTML support allows you to flow your HTML from one area to another - across pages or columns or both. A vast range of options gives you full control over the HTML rendering process and DOM.

In terms of features, probably most notably, the Gecko engine supports repeated table headers and footers. It is also extremely good on SVG and AJAX for charts and maps. The MSHTML engine tends to be faster and provides a more literal screen based output. Gecko generally supports modern HTML features better than MSHTML.
title: ABCpdf .NET Gecko Runtime
